== Description == <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
This simple calculator determines the minimum average thrust required to maintain a 5:1 thrust to weight ratio.

== Usage == <!--T:5-->

</translate>
[[File:Calc_thrust_to_weight.png]]
<translate>

<!--T:6-->
# There are several ways to invoke the command: 
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Rocket_Calculator.svg|16px]] [[Rocket_Thrust_To_Weight_Calculator|Thrust To Weight Calculator]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Rocket → Calculators → [[Image:Rocket_Calculator.svg|16px]] Thrust To Weight Calculator}} option from the menu.
# Enter the weight of your rocket.

== Calculation == <!--T:7-->

<!--T:8-->
Thrust to weight is calculated using the following formula:

<!--T:9-->
::<math>T_{min} = 5mg</math>

<!--T:10-->
where

<!--T:11-->
::<math>T_{min} = </math> recommended minimum average thrust<br>
::<math>m = </math> mass of the rocket<br>
::<math>g = 9.807\, m/s^2</math>, acceleration due to gravity<br>

=== Units === <!--T:12-->

<!--T:13-->
Calculations are done using metric units, but will display in your preferred units. Values can also be entered using any supported units by including the units with the value (''eg'' 5 oz, or 23.2 g)


